100 Most Influential Black Americans - Ebony magazine [12]
14th Best American Entrepreneur, Success Magazine, 1998[11]
Business Person of the Year for Missouri, Small Business Administration[4]
Company of the Year, Black Enterprise, 1999[11]
Entrepreneur of the Year, Black Enterprise, 2000[11]
Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year, 1998[11]
Five time winner, Fast 50 Awards[11]
Granville T. Woods Award for Outstanding CEO, 1997[11]
Honorary doctorate in humane letters, Harris Stowe State College [2]
Honorary doctorate in humane letters, Lindenwood University[2]
Minority Small Business Person of the Year, Small Business Administration, 1997, 1998[11]
Phoenix Award, St. Louis Minority Business Council, 2000[11]
Small Business Association Hall of Fame, 2001[11]
The American Marketing Association 1996 Distinguished Executive[7]
Top 100 Industrial/Service Companies, Black Enterprise, 11th in 1998, 6th in 1999, 1st in 2000 and 2001[11]
Top 100 List of St. Louis Leaders, 2002 [11]
Top Minority Entrepreneur, Small Business Administration, 1998[11]
Black Engineer of the Year, BEYA STEM Conference, 2012[13]
Horatio Alger Award, Horatio Alger Association of Distinguished Americans, 2014[14]

