featured


        
        Stewards donate laptops to City Academy
    


Special to The American

Apr 12, 2012
 3





























































































City Academy sixth graders accepted a surprise gift recently from the David L. Steward family: brand new laptop computers that they will take with them after graduation and as they begin the next chapter of their educational journeys into secondary schools for the 2012-2013.
“We are very pleased to have the opportunity to reward these hard-working students with the laptops,” said David L. Steward Sr., Founder and Chairman of the Board of the St. Louis-based company World Wide Technology, Inc.
“City Academy’s mission to prepare students for the highest-possible level of academic success aligns closely with my family’s priorities for the community. This gift is a gesture of congratulations, and we hope it also serves as an encouragement for these students to continue working hard.”
City Academy’s current class of sixth graders will graduate on May 23, 2012. They have been accepted to some of the area’s most competitive secondary schools, including Crossroads, Chaminade, Villa Duchesne, Visitation Academy, John Burroughs, MICDS, St. Louis Priory, Westminster, Central Christian and Whitfield.





City Academy is located at 4175 North Kingshighway. Founded in 1999, the school is the only private, independent elementary school in St. Louis providing scholarship support to 100 percent of its students.





















































